==English==

===Noun===
'''delinquent'''
# one who [[disobey]]s rules.
# a term applied to [[royalist]]s by their opponents in the English Civil War 1642  - 1645. Charles I was known as the chief delinquent.
# refers to a person who is late to pay or fails to pay a debt or other financial obligation, like a mortgage, car payment or credit card. Fred is delinquent in making his car payment. 
